Jessica Hardy, 23, from Hereford, was so desperate to remove her former flame's name from her forearm when she tried to burn it off with acid .
She applied acid without diluting it with water or reading instructions .
Six painful applications left Jessica's skin red raw and scabby - and the tattoo remained visible .
The mother-of-one said: 'I'm desperate to get rid of it, I have bad dreams about it'